# Use NCEI API to pull data from the station @ Aginskoe, Russia
aginskoe_api_url = (
           "https://www.ncei.noaa.gov/access/services/data/v1"
           "?dataset=daily-summaries&"
           "dataTypes=TMIN,TMAX,PRCP&"
           "stations=RSM00030859&"
           "startDate=1936-01-01&"
           "endDate=2023-01-19&"
           "includeStationName=true&"
           #"includeStationLocation=1&"
           "units=standard"
           )

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10,6))

x_values = mdates.date2num(barrow_feb.index)


ax.scatter(x_values,
           barrow_feb["TMIN"],
           label="Temperature Data")

# Fit a linear regression model
slope, intercept = np.polyfit(x_values, barrow_feb["TMIN"], 1)
trendline = slope * x_values + intercept

ax.plot(x_values, trendline, color='red', label="Trendline")
ax.plot(x_values, barrow_feb["TMIN"])

# Formatting x-axis as dates
ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(mdates.YearLocator(2))
ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%Y'))

# Add text box with slope value
slope_text = f"Slope: {slope:.5f}"
ax.text(0.8, 0.7, slope_text, transform=ax.transAxes, fontsize=12,
        verticalalignment='top', bbox=dict(boxstyle='round', facecolor='whitesmoke', alpha=0.9))



ax.set(title="Maximum daily low temperature (February)\nBarrow, AK (1994-2024)",
       ylabel="Temperature (F)")

ax.legend()  # Add legend to display labels

plt.show()
